title: Strange multiplication behavior
body_html:
The following code gives two different outputs in two settings.

Top window: independent IPython Console
Bottom window: at a breakpoint within a longer script I am using currently

The result in top window is correct (and same as numpy). I am using version 0.4.0a0+f8439c2 along with Python 3.6.4 though this does not seem to be an issue with the version.

body:
The following code gives two different outputs in two settings.

![Strange multiplication behavior](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6690052/37379625-bda87482-270a-11e8-9087-ee1ca6908cea.png)

Top window: independent IPython Console
Bottom window: at a breakpoint within a longer script I am using currently

The result in top window is correct (and same as numpy). I am using version `0.4.0a0+f8439c2` along with Python `3.6.4` though this does not seem to be an issue with the version.
